<div id="c1">
<p>Swartz 1, Gruber 0 ;-)</p>

<p>Funny quote (from Gruber):
&#8220;ANYONE ELSE FROM GOOGLE. No credibility within Apple regarding design, no experience with hardware products.&#8221;</p>

<p>It&#8217;s amazing just how blind Google is to design. Their web interfaces are generally both confusing and ugly. (Their initial search page design is the exception. As is the current redesign.) How do they do it? Can they not just hire interface designers?</p>

<p>Ira Glass suggests if you want to do good creative work, you first need good taste. That&#8217;s not the sort of thing anyone is going to teach you at art school. But it&#8217;s very true. And under-rated. Jon Ive it is.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="bradbell.tv">bradbell.tv</a>
 on July 23, 2011 <a href="#c1" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
